HTML documentation flow:
<a><span><em><img>
inline elements can't take the width,height, margin-top,bottom property except image

block level elements push other elements to new line

p,h1
we can't put block level elements inside inline elements inverse is possible

:Display Property-->> we can use display inline property to make block elements behave like inline elements

to hide a element display should be none

for selecting first child: 
p:first-child{
	property;
	}
p:last-of-child{

}

p:nth-child(5){

}

#q > p{			//to select first level p

}

#q + p{			// to select first p after #q id element

}

#q ~ p{		//to slect all p after id element #q

}

browser starting reading css file from bottom

specificity rule

